JULII
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1751AB67FF3067CB9FD61BB8" blockId="20.[164,779,937,1541]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1751AB67FF3067CB9F511CD4" baseAuthorityName="Daams" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[164,346,937,958]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="julii">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1751AB67FF3067CB9F511CD4" box="[164,346,937,958]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Simplomys julii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species in the fossil record. It has not been studied since 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6C1751AB67FD9467AA9CA91CB4" author="Daams R" box="[512,674,968,990]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" pagination="13 - 26" refId="ref16583" refString="Daams R. 1989. Miscellaneous Gliridae from the Miocene of the Calatayud-Teruel basin, Aragon, Spain. Scripta Geologica 89: 13 - 26." type="journal article" year="1989">Daams (1989)</bibRefCitation>
.Material from other than the 
<typeStatus id="54C7883F1751AB67FE0967859FC51C96" box="[413,462,999,1020]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">type</typeStatus>
locality was not described until the revision of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1751AB67FE0060679FEF1B70" baseAuthorityName="Daams" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[404,484,1029,1050]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="julii">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1751AB67FE0060679FEF1B70" box="[404,484,1029,1050]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">S. julii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Aragonian 
<typeStatus id="54C7883F1751AB67FD4D60649D011B71" box="[729,778,1030,1051]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">type</typeStatus>
area by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6C1751AB67FE9A60469C1C1B50" author="Garcia-Paredes I" box="[270,535,1060,1082]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" refId="ref17607" refString="Garcia-Paredes I. 2006. Patrones evolutivos de los Gliridae (Rodentia, Mammalia) del Mioceno inferior y medio del area tipo del Aragoniense (Cuenca de Calatayud - Montalban). Unpublished D. Phil. Thesis, Universidad Complutense de Madrid." type="book" year="2006">García-Paredes (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. This study demonstrated a trend toward size increase of the cheek teeth (
<figureCitation id="13472A181751AB67FF6760039F491B1D" box="[243,322,1121,1143]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1792,1811]" captionTargetBox="[198,1368,1026,1762]" captionTargetId="graphics-199@17.[236,1368,1028,1741]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 10. Temporal distribution of average surface of the upper and lower cheek teeth in species of Simplomys gen. nov. from the Aragonian type area (Calatayud–Montalbán basin, Spain). Only localities with at least five measurable specimens of each element are included. Horizontal bars represent two times the standard deviation. Modified after García-Paredes, 2006." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443107/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) and gives for the first time detailed descriptions of the premolars and lower third molars of this species, showing its high degree of simplification and reduction (
<figureCitation id="13472A181751AB67FE1960DF9FC41BB8" box="[397,463,1213,1235]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="14.[164,243,1233,1252]" captionTargetBox="[323,1284,195,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-205@14.[323,1284,195,1203]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 7. Simplomys julii (Daams, 1989) from Artesilla (Fig. 7A–H; J–L; N–O) and San Roque 3 (Fig. 7I, M) (collection MNCN). A, P4 ART-2444. B, M1 ART-3. C, M2 ART-28. D, M3 ART-21. E, P4 ART-2447. F, M1 ART-4 holotype. G, M2 ART-13. H, M3 ART-1176. I, p4 SR3-803. J, m1 ART-16. K, m2 ART-14. L, m3 ART-1036. M, p4 SR3-604. N, m1 ART-22. O, m2 ART-27. Right side specimens underlined. Holotype in italics." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443099" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443099/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC3369D1751AB67FF2860B99FFA196F" blockId="20.[164,779,937,1541]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1751AB67FF2860B99F7B1B9A" baseAuthorityName="Daams" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[188,368,1243,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="julii">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1751AB67FF2860B99F7B1B9A" box="[188,368,1243,1264]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Simplomys julii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered to have a short stratigraphical distribution restricted to the lower Aragonian (Lower Miocene) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6C1751AB67FD9E617B9ED61A27" author="Daams R &amp; de Bruijn H" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" pagination="3 - 50" refId="ref16874" refString="Daams R, de Bruijn H. 1995. A classification of the Gliridae (Rodentia) on the basis of dental morphology. Hystrix (n. s.) 6: 3 - 50." type="journal article" year="1995">Daams &amp; de Bruijn, 1995</bibRefCitation>
; Daams, 1999). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B6C1751AB67FE0E61559C911A27" author="Garcia-Paredes I" box="[410,666,1335,1357]" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" refId="ref17607" refString="Garcia-Paredes I. 2006. Patrones evolutivos de los Gliridae (Rodentia, Mammalia) del Mioceno inferior y medio del area tipo del Aragoniense (Cuenca de Calatayud - Montalban). Unpublished D. Phil. Thesis, Universidad Complutense de Madrid." type="book" year="2006">García-Paredes (2006)</bibRefCitation>
extended the stratigraphical distribution of this species to the upper Ramblian (Lower Miocene) and part of the middle Aragonian (Middle Miocene) (
<tableCitation id="C6FE03261751AB67FDF761F19CB31AC3" box="[611,696,1427,1449]" captionStart="Table 5" captionStartId="10.[164,228,198,217]" captionText="Table 5. Stratigraphical distribution of the species of Simplomys gen. nov. Series; continental stages; Mammal Neogene Zones (MN zones) proposed for Europe by Mein (1975, 1990) and revised by De Bruijn et al. (1992); and local biostratigraphical scale after Daams et al. (1999)" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Table 5</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D1E1751AB67FD4061F19F211AAC" baseAuthorityName="Daams" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Simplomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="20" pageNumber="642" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="julii">
<emphasis id="B908EA8F1751AB67FD4061F19F211AAC" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Simplomys julii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found only in 
<collectingCountry id="F36B760D1751AB67FDAB61D39C8A1AAD" box="[575,641,1457,1479]" name="Spain" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">Spain</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36B760D1751AB67FD2F61D09D011AAD" box="[699,778,1458,1479]" name="France" pageId="20" pageNumber="642">France</collectingCountry>
(see Supporting Information Appendix S1 for details on localities and references).
</paragraph>
